Author: Maciej Beresewicz [aut, cre] (ORCID:
    <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8281-4301>), Igor Kołodziej [aut, ctb],
    Mateusz Iwaniuk [aut, ctb]
Maintainer: Maciej Beresewicz <maciej.beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl>
Description: Methods to estimate finite-population parameters under nonresponse that is not missing at
    random (NMAR, nonignorable). Includes empirical likelihood (Qin, Leung and Shao (2002)
    <doi:10.1198/016214502753479338>), exponential tilting (Riddles, Kim and Im (2016)
    <doi:10.1093/jssam/smv047>), and induced logistic regression (Li, Qin and Liu (2023)
    <doi:10.1111/biom.13881>). Supports independent samples and complex survey designs via objects
    from the 'survey' package. Provides diagnostics and optional variance estimates.
